<h2>When does Prowl send alerts?</h2>
<p>
  Prowl only sends alerts for <strong>high-severity issues</strong> — problems that directly prevent customers from purchasing. This keeps your inbox clean and ensures every alert is worth your attention.
</p>
<p>
  There are two paths to alerting:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>AI-confirmed issues</strong> — If AI visual analysis confirms the issue with high confidence, you get an alert immediately on first detection.</li>
  <li><strong>Other high-severity issues</strong> — These are re-checked on the next scan before alerting, to reduce false alarms.</li>
</ul>

<h2>What's in an alert email?</h2>
<p>Each alert email includes:</p>
<ul>
  <li>A <strong>screenshot</strong> of the page showing the issue</li>
  <li>A clear <strong>explanation</strong> of what went wrong</li>
  <li>A <strong>suggested fix</strong> you can act on</li>
  <li>A link to <strong>acknowledge</strong> the issue (stops further emails for that issue)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Configuring alerts</h2>
<p>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> in the Prowl app to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Set a custom email address for alert delivery (defaults to your store owner email)</li>
  <li>Enable or disable email alerts</li>
  <li>Enable or disable Shopify admin notifications</li>
</ul>

<h2>Stopping alerts for a known issue</h2>
<p>
  If you're aware of an issue and working on a fix, click <strong>"Acknowledge"</strong> on the issue detail page or in the alert email. This stops repeat notifications for that specific issue. The issue will still be tracked on your dashboard.
</p>

<h2>Will I get re-alerted?</h2>
<p>
  Once acknowledged, Prowl will not send more emails about that issue. If the issue is resolved and then re-detected in a future scan, it will be treated as a new issue and you'll receive a fresh alert.
</p>
